# Trivy ignore file for Fulcrum Boundary.
#
# The fixtures/ tree holds intentional, synthetic red-team payloads with NO real
# secrets (see fixtures/README.md). They are decoys the test suite uses to prove
# Boundary denies the dangerous action; nothing is read, executed, or sent. The
# entries below stop Trivy's secret/misconfig scanners from false-positiving on
# a fresh clone.

# Suppress secret-scanner findings under the fixtures tree.
# (Trivy matches these glob paths against the scanned file path.)
fixtures/**
fixtures/editboundary/**
fixtures/editboundary/redteam/**
fixtures/external-inventory/**

# The synthetic .env decoys trigger the generic API-key secret rule by design.
generic-api-key
